{"word":"εἰσδύνω","slug":"εἰσδύνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εἰσδύνω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <el>εἰς-δύομαι</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <el>δύω</el>\n<el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-δύσομαι</el>) (with aor2 <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <el>-έδῡν</el>) (<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>-δέδῡκα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to get</i> or <i>go into</i>, with <el>εἰς</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to enter</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>subire</el>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—of feelings, <el>εἰσέδυ με μνήμη κακῶν</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <el>δεινόν τι ἐσέδυνε σφίσι</el> great fear <i>came upon</i> them, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}